list.name: Changes
list.comment: First semi working iteration of the ai integration thing. Basically now it can take natural language with the name of a date and output natural language of the descriptions and titles. It for some reason tries to contextualize that information. It also can't take the name of the month instead of the number. Sometimes works when provided with nth month instead of date. It also interprets dates as dd/mm/yy, which is interesting (despite their name, Nous Research is based in NY). Possibly a remnant from mixtrel? Next is to add this but for creating events.

task.summary: created project and added code that makes/appends to a text file with the correct number of days(leap years included I think) calendar. Next will try to figure out how to parse between everything and add events.
Added a new file to add events, and add them to the calendar on the correct day
bug fixes on make_new_event.py, started working on read_events_from_date.py
